</p>
<p>Try it again. Awesome, this time, we get blocked.</p>
<p>If you want to be <em>extra</em> careful, you could add some try-catch logic to your checkout
code <em>just</em> to prevent the edge-case where the code becomes <em>invalid</em> between
the time of adding it to your cart and checking out. But either way, Stripe will <em>never</em>
allow an invalid coupon to be used.</p>

    
